The Team | Basalt


































 Home / The Team





Rob Gregor
Managing Partner
			London


Rob Gregor
Managing Partner
Tel: +44 20 7766 3350 Email: rob.gregor@basaltinfra.com
Rob is responsible for the overall management of the Firm, is a member of the Investment Committee and has 25 years of infrastructure experience. Rob is currently a director of UPPCO, Wightlink, Alkane Energy and Texas Microgrid.
Previously, Rob was Head of European Infrastructure at AMP, where he was responsible for managing the European infrastructure investment business, which he was instrumental in founding in 2005. At AMP, he oversaw transaction origination and execution, portfolio management and asset management for AMP’s European managed infrastructure funds. Rob was director of a number of AMP’s European portfolio companies including Alpha Trains, Compañía Logística De Hidrocarburos (“CLH”), Thames Water and SMIF. Rob served as an alternate director of Wales and West Utilities. Prior to joining AMP in 1997, Rob worked for Bankers Trust, TNT Limited, and Ernst and Young.
Rob holds a Bachelor of Commerce from the University of Canberra and a Master of Commerce (Accounting and Finance) from the University of Sydney in Australia, and a Graduate Diploma in Applied Finance and Investment from the Financial Services Institute of Australasia. Rob is also a Member of the UK Institute of Company Directors. 



Steven Lowry
Partner
			London


Steven Lowry
Partner
Tel: +44 20 7766 3355 Email: steven.lowry@basaltinfra.com
Steven is responsible for advising on the origination, execution and management of assets, predominantly in Western Europe, and is a member of the Investment Committee. Steven has 21 years industry experience and is currently a director of McEwan Power, Wightlink and Alkane Energy.
Previously, Steven was Director of European Infrastructure at AMP where he led, executed and managed transport and social infrastructure investments for AMP’s European managed infrastructure funds. At AMP, Steven served as a director of Angel Trains and Alpha Trains. Prior to joining AMP in 2007, Steven worked as Head of Infrastructure Equity and Advisory, Europe at Commonwealth Bank of Australia in London, focusing on the transport and social infrastructure sectors. He additionally founded and led the social infrastructure team at Commonwealth Bank of Australia Limited (“CBA”) in Sydney. Prior to working for CBA, Steven worked for Halifax Bank of Scotland PLC in infrastructure project finance. His 21 years of experience in leading transactions for debt, advisory and equity investments in airports (Sydney Airport), roads, ports (Dalrymple Bay), rolling stock (Angel Trains) and social infrastructure (Forth Valley Hospital) has provided him with strong project management skills and a detailed understanding of managing complex transaction processes, skills that are essential in executing infrastructure transactions. 
Steven holds a Bachelor of Science (Honours) from St. Andrews University in the UK and qualified as a Chartered Accountant with PricewaterhouseCoopers. Steven is also a Member of the UK Institute of Company Directors.



Jeff Neil
Partner
			New York


Jeff Neil
Partner
Tel: +1 646 661 3901 Email: jeff.neil@basaltinfra.com
Jeff is based in New York and is responsible for origination and ongoing management of North American infrastructure investments.  He is also a member of the Investment Committee (appointed by the U.S. sub-adviser). Jeff is currently a director of UPPCO and Texas Microgrid.
Prior to the establishment of Basalt, Jeff was Investment Director of European Infrastructure at AMP where he was responsible for the origination and execution of infrastructure investments in Europe, focused in particular on utilities and energy transactions, for AMP’s European managed funds. While at AMP, Jeff originated and led the AMP execution team for investments in a major monopoly products distribution and storage network in Spain and managed the execution of AMP’s European portfolio investment in Thames Water, one of the UK’s largest water and wastewater networks. Prior to joining AMP in 2005, Jeff worked for Duke Energy, originating and executing structured energy commodity transactions and for Enron, where he focused on asset development and acquisitions in Europe, South America and the Middle East. Jeff has 23 years of experience, including 20 years’ experience as a principal investor in Europe, the Americas and the Middle East, with experience focused primarily on the energy sector. 
Jeff holds a Bachelor of Arts from The American University in Washington, DC. 



Michael Cowell
Chief Operating Officer
			London


Michael Cowell
Chief Operating Officer
Tel: +44 20 7766 3360 Email: michael.cowell@basaltinfra.com
Michael is responsible for the administration and operations of the Firm. Previously, Michael was European Investment Manager at AMP, where he was predominantly responsible for the operational management of AMP’s European managed funds and also worked as an asset manager on several of the European portfolio’s investments, including Wales and West Utilities and Thames Water. Michael joined AMP in 2003 and was initially employed as an investment manager in risk and operations for the Private Equity and Infrastructure divisions, following which he managed AMP Life’s portfolio of private equity and infrastructure investments. Michael is currently a director of McEwan Power and Alkane Energy.
Michael has over 23 years of industry experience, holds a Bachelor of Science (Honours) from The Nottingham Trent University and is a fellow member of the Chartered Association of Certified Accountants.



Rob Keough
Senior Principal
			New York


Rob Keough
Senior Principal
Tel: +1 646 661 3905 Email: rob.keough@basaltinfra.com
Rob joined Basalt in 2013 and is located in the New York office. Rob is responsible for advising on the origination and ongoing management of infrastructure investments, primarily in North America. Rob is currently a director of UPPCO. Previously, Rob was Managing Director at John Hancock Life Insurance Company, where he was most recently portfolio manager of John Hancock’s infrastructure equity portfolio. During his tenure at John Hancock, he played a lead in building and managing an infrastructure portfolio comprised of direct investments, co-investments, and equity fund investments in power generation, electric transmission and distribution, oil & gas midstream, utilities, toll roads, airports, ports and rail in North America, the UK and Continental Europe. Prior to joining John Hancock in 2001, Rob was an attorney at Bingham McCutchen in Boston and PhelpsDunbar in Mississippi.
Rob holds a Bachelor of Science in finance (magna cum laude) from Syracuse University and a Juris Doctor from Vanderbilt University.



John Hanna
Principal
			London


John Hanna
Principal
Tel: +44 20 7766 3366 Email: john.hanna@basaltinfra.com
John joined Basalt at its inception and is located in the London office. John advises on the origination, execution, management and operation of investments for the Firm. John is currently a director of McEwan Power and Wightlink. Previously, John was a transaction director within Balfour Beatty Investments and has 15 years of infrastructure investment and advisory experience. While at Balfour Beatty Investments, John was involved in the origination and acquisition of infrastructure assets in sectors such as airports and offshore transmission and has been actively involved in the management of investments across Balfour Beatty Investments’ wider portfolio. Prior to joining Balfour Beatty Investments, John worked in the infrastructure financing teams at both PricewaterhouseCoopers and KPMG, advising private sector bidders and government bodies on transactions across the transport and social infrastructure sectors.
John holds a Bachelor of Arts from Manchester Metropolitan University.



David Greenblatt
Principal
			New York


David Greenblatt
Principal
Tel: +1 646 661 3902
David joined Basalt in 2011 and is located in the New York office. David advises on the origination, execution, management and operation of investments for the Firm, with a particular focus on the North American market. David is currently a director of Texas Microgrid and has 14 years of experience in infrastructure investment and advisory services. Previously, David worked as a strategic consultant at Parsons Brinckerhoff, where he advised financial and strategic investors on transactions in the transport sector. David focused on econometric-based demand and life cycle cost analysis of large transport and power generation assets in North America.
David holds a Bachelor of Arts from Connecticut College and a Masters degree from Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT), with a focus on Applied Economics. David is a fluent speaker of Mandarin.



Joe Galan
Asset Manager
			New York


Joe Galan
Asset Manager
Tel: +1 646 661 3900Email: joe.galan@basaltinfra.com
 Joe Galan recently joined Basalt as Asset Manager, based in the New York office. He is focused principally on asset management of Basalt’s North American portfolio investments.
Prior to joining Basalt in 2017, Joe was Senior Vice president at GE Capital - Energy Financial Services where he led investment underwriting and execution of transactions in the power renewables and energy infrastructure sectors in the US and abroad. Prior to GE, Joe worked for Ashmore Energy where he focused on capital expansions, turn-around efforts and acquisition financing on power and gas infrastructure assets and for Enron in the areas of asset management, M&A, and project and structured finance supporting the commodities business and equity investments in power and energy sectors.   Joe has 20+ years of experience in the areas of asset management, project and structured finance, investment underwriting and capital market transactions.
Joe holds a BBA in Accounting from the University of Texas, a MBA in Finance from Tulane University, a CPA designation, and is a member of the Global Association of Risk Professionals.



Markus Geisselmann
Vice President
			Munich


Markus Geisselmann
Vice President
Tel: +49 179 5008 992 Email: markus.geisselmann@basaltinfra.com
Markus joined Basalt in January 2013 and is located in Munich. Markus advises on the origination, execution, management and operation of investments for the Firm, with a particular focus on the German-speaking markets of Germany, Austria and Switzerland. He has over 21 years of infrastructure investment experience and before joining Basalt he was Bid Director at Balfour Beatty Investments’ Munich office where he was responsible for the origination and acquisition of infrastructure assets in Central and Western Europe. Prior to joining Balfour Beatty Investments, Markus worked for the infrastructure investment department of major Austrian and German contractors (Alpine Mayreder and Walter Bau) and Kreditananstakt für Wiederaufbau (KFW).
Markus holds a degree in business administration from Pforzheim University.



Jennifer Katz
Vice President
			New York


Jennifer Katz
Vice President
Tel: +1 646 661 3904 Email: jennifer.katz@basaltinfra.com
Jennifer joined Basalt in 2013 and is located in the New York office. Jennifer assists the Partners with the origination, execution, management and operation of North American investment opportunities. Jennifer began her career at AllCapital and continued on with the same team at Abatis Capital. She also worked as a senior consultant for Sigma Energy Solutions. Jennifer has 9 years of infrastructure experience, having specialized in North American regulated utilities and energy generation investment opportunities, including both conventional and renewable technologies.
Jennifer holds a BA in Astrophysics with a concentration in Mathematics from Columbia University.



Wil Jones
Vice President
			London


Wil Jones
Vice President
Tel: +44 20 7766 3352 Email: wil.jones@basaltinfra.com
Wil joined Basalt in March 2014 and is located in the London office. Wil focuses on the origination, execution, management and operation of investments, predominantly in Western Europe. Prior to joining Basalt, Wil spent over four years at Deloitte where he specialised in business modelling within Corporate Finance. Wil worked as part of a team to design, develop and test complex models for a diverse range of clients including infrastructure related projects.
Wil is a qualified Chartered Accountant and holds a BSc (Hons) in Mathematics from the University of Manchester.



Amrita Jaijee
General Counsel
			London


Amrita Jaijee
General Counsel
Tel: +44 20 7766 3361 Email: amrita.jaijee@basaltinfra.com
Amrita joined Basalt in February 2012 and is General Counsel, responsible for all legal matters, and in addition is Chief Compliance Officer. Previously, Amrita spent over four years with Macquarie with a focus on principal investment, financing, asset management and support to the financial advisory businesses, primarily in the Infrastructure and Real Estate sectors across the EMEA region. Prior to that, Amrita was part of the European Transaction and Securitisation Group at Citi focusing on structuring and negotiation of financing. Amrita trained and qualified with Clifford Chance with a particular focus on Pan-European Acquisition Financing transactions.
Amrita holds an MA in Jurisprudence from Oxford University and is a member of the Law Society of England and Wales.



Andy Friend
Chairman of the Investment Committee
			London


Andy Friend
Chairman of the Investment Committee
Tel: +44 20 7766 3370 Email: andy.friend@basaltinfra.com
Andy chairs the Investment Committee. Andy is an experienced Chief Executive Officer and has been involved in the infrastructure sector for more than 30 years. Previously, Andy was CEO and Managing Director of Infrastructure at John Laing plc, where he played a leading role in the restructuring and growth of the group as a leading investor prior to its 2006 acquisition by Henderson for £1.0 billion. Prior to John Laing plc, Andy worked at Macquarie in the UK as an Associate Director, a position he assumed in 1997. Andy held a succession of senior management roles at the City of Melbourne focused on economic and service development, culminating in his appointment as Chief Executive in 1995. Andy is an experienced Non-Executive Director having served on the Boards of Partnerships UK, Financial Security Assurance (UK) Ltd, the Department for Transport High Speed Two Ltd. and numerous project companies in the rail, airports and utility sectors. He is currently a Non-Executive Chairman of the investment committee of the InfraMed fund and a member of the City University Council.
Andy holds a Master of Arts from Cambridge University. He is also a graduate member of the Australian Institute of Company Directors and a former Companion of the Chartered Management Institute.



Marcus Berg
